A man who allegedly broke into a home and raped a 25-year-old woman was arrested by police after he fell asleep in the victim s house. Police spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said police in Waterval in Limpopo arrested a 27-year-old man after he fell asleep in his victim s house after raping her. It is alleged that the victim was sleeping in the early hours of [Saturday] at about 3.30am when the suspect broke the door entered the house threatened her and raped her Ngoepe said. After this ordeal the suspect fell asleep (and) the vicrtim escaped and called the police he said. The police reacted swiftly and found the suspect still asleep and arrested him said Ngoepe. He said the suspect would appear in the Waterval Magistrate s Court on Monday on charges of housebreaking and rape. Ngoepe said police investigations were ongoing. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share